[Raising community awareness of this disease is one issue. Learning
biosecurity issues in clinics and shelters is another method of
control. But why did the veterinarians not recommend vaccination?
There are effective vaccinations against this disease. Why are the
community and area not being encouraged to vaccinate their animals? -
Mod.TG]

